RACE.RACE_TEXT: FAIR GROUNDS RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 60. Claiming Purse 15000. FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 117 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since December 27 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PSEUDOSCIENCE set the pace along the inside around the first turn, but was headed by an outer bidding foe with five furlongs to go, vied until failing to keep pace entering the far turn, yet stalked from the pocket around that bend, searched for racing room while sustaining stride in upper stretch, mounted a rail re-challenge in the final furlong as the leaders tired, and forged an advantage late. DEBS PRAYER pressed two wide, led down the backstretch, showed the way from an outer bidder around the far turn while remaining a bit off of the rail, clung to a margin in upper stretch, dug in between horses in the final furlong, but was bested by an inner bidder late. GUANAJUATO broke a bit awkwardly, tracked two wide under a tight rein around the first turn, pursued from between horses around the far turn before tipping four wide entering the lane, and offered a mild kick to attempt a bid leaving the furlong grounds, but was outfinished by an inner rival late while being denied place. MYLIES STAR bobbled leaving the gates, leaned outwardly while recovering causing tight quarters for an outer rival, checked once in tight quarters himself inside of a rival entering the first turn, tugged to a tracking position around that bend, but was shuffled back entering the far turn, shifted three wide turning for home, fanned six wide entering the lane, but lacked a rally. T J'S FIRST checked from crowded quarters between horses at the start, settled off of the pace in the two path, shifted out four wide nearing the backstretch, inched closer outside of foes approaching the far turn, but failed to threaten before tiring entering the lane. COME WHAT MAE broke out, stalked three wide, bid into the far turn, vied between horses while hanging on her left lead in upper stretch, but weakened leaving the furlong grounds. ZEEROCK trailed along the inside, then two wide into the far turn, got floated seven wide entering the lane, and failed to factor.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: KEYS INCLUDED stalked outside of the pace setter, assumed command in the three path turning for home, and drew off under mild urging. IRONMAN RICHIE ducked in slightly while establishing a clear margin early on, required right handed correction from the rider to keep from acting up again nearing the backstretch, shifted out a bit while showing a way at the nine sixteenths, then offered little resistance to an outer rival's bid approaching the five sixteenths pole, and weakened. EXCLAIM brushed an inner rival at the start, laid off of the pace in the three to five paths around the first turn, chased four wide around the far turn, then lacked a rally between horses. COSTELLO'S KITTEN tracked three wide, lost position entering the backstretch, regained stride when roused between horses at the half mile pole, but only managed to chase the top pair around the far turn before weakening. OGRE'S LION KING tracked along the inside, chased around the far turn, and faded.
